    <h1>Oversec is your Encryption-Swiss-Army-Knife.</h1>
    <p>Oversec allows you to transparently encrypt and decrypt any text in any
      app - use it to exchange encrypted chat- or email messages or store your
      own encrypted notes on your phone.<br>
      <br>
      Oversec is completely agnostic of the app being used, it works with
      Whatsapp, Line, Snapchat or any other chat app. It also works with the
      Gmail app or any other Email app.</p>
    <p>End-to-End Encryption was yesterday. Oversec introduces "Eye-to-Eye"
      encryption. Encrypted data is only decrypted when shown on the screen and
      only _while_ it is shown! No cleartext is ever persisted and thus cannot
      be extracted from the file system or accidentially be uploaded into the
      cloud.</p>
    <h2>How it works:</h2>
    <p>Oversec constantly monitors the text on your screen (via the
      Accessibility API). When it finds an encrypted text, it tries to decrypt
      it and then shows the decrypted text as an overlay in place of the
      encrypted text.</p>
    <p>In order to encrypt a text, Oversec shows a button next to any active
      text-input field. After having entered the cleartext in the input field,
      pressing this button lets Oversec read the clear-text, encrypt it and put
      back the encrypted text into the input field. It is now ready to be sent
      in the underlying app.</p>
    <p>Oversec also features a unique way of encoding the encrypted messages. It
      stores the encrypted text in invisible (zero-wodth) chracters and let's
      you add decoy text at the end. This way, a message will just e.g. show
      "How are you today" with no visible sign of any encryption, whereas in
      reality it contains an encrypted message "Meet at PB Hotel now".</p>
